  "text": "5.1 Storing the data set Unlike for binary relation mining algorithms, it is not possible to speed up the extraction by storing for each element e of D 1 , . . . , D n the projection of the input data set R on e (usually called \"tidset\"). The use of sophisticated data structures like FP-Trees [CITATION_1] remains an open problem because of the multiple attributes to be considered and the need to use each one during the enumeration.",
